DOM
=====================
1) DOM is API Interface provied by browser.
2) When a webpage is loaded.Browser creates a DOM of the page.
3) With the DOM.Js can accecss and change all elements of an HTML Document


JavaScript POWER
======================
1) JS can change all HTML elemetns & Attributes in the webpage
2) JS can change the CSS style in the webpage
3) JS can remove existing HTML elements and Attributes
4) JS can add new HTML elements and Attributes
5) JS can react to all existing HTML elemetns events in the webpage
6) JS can create new HTML events in HTML page